---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ShowcaseCard from '../components/ShowcaseCard.astro';
import { homepageFeaturedCharacters, homepageFeaturedMonsters } from '../data/showcase';
---

<BaseLayout title="Via Occulta | A 1-bit occult shared-world JRPG">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="shell hero-grid">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">A 1-bit occult shared-world JRPG</p>
        <h1>Hidden roads, shrine bells, guild fire, and the things waiting below them.</h1>
        <p>
          Via Occulta is a monochrome dark-fantasy JRPG world built around overhead exploration,
          cursed routes, dungeon expeditions, workshop labor, and the slow restoration of a world
          that is quietly being rerouted from underneath itself.
        </p>
        <div class="pill-row">
          <span class="pill">Tenebrio discovers</span>
          <span class="pill">Luciphilus fights</span>
          <span class="pill">Opiphilus builds</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-sheet">
        <div class="feature-grid">
          {homepageFeaturedCharacters.slice(0, 2).map((page) => <ShowcaseCard page={page} href={`characters/${page.slug}`} />)}
          {homepageFeaturedMonsters.slice(0, 2).map((page) => <ShowcaseCard page={page} href={`monsters/${page.slug}`} />)}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="shell">
      <p class="eyebrow">The world premise</p>
      <h2>The old roads have vanished from the maps.</h2>
      <div class="three-up">
        <article class="info-card">
          <h3>The Viae Occultae</h3>
          <p>
            The hidden roads once linked shrines, caves, chapels, guild cellars, market doors, and
            sealed underways through a compact of rites, crystals, charters, and remembered names.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="info-card">
          <h3>The Quiet Collapse</h3>
          <p>
            The world is not ending in a single blaze. Its routes are being quietly rewritten.
            Towns wake to find wells opening into catacombs and chapel doors leading to rooms that
            should not exist.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="info-card">
          <h3>The Shared-World Loop</h3>
          <p>
            Tenebrio finds the road, Luciphilus survives what guards it, and Opiphilus turns the
            recovered fragments into something a town can use again.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="shell split">
      <div class="summary-panel">
        <p class="eyebrow">First region</p>
        <h3>The Pilgrim Verge</h3>
        <p>
          The first region is a compact shrine-town frontier: Greybell Shrine, The Broken Road,
          Mistfall Chapel, The Underwell, The Chapel Undercrypt, The Guild Hearth, and The Old
          Crystal Gate.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Greybell Shrine: the failing road-bell hub</li>
          <li>Mistfall Chapel: a cursed shrine ruin</li>
          <li>The Guild Hearth: the craft heart of the town</li>
          <li>The Old Crystal Gate: the first recovered threshold</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          The opening arc, <strong>The Bell That Forgot the Road</strong>, is the cleanest way to
          understand Via Occulta. A shrine bell stops ringing. The roads beyond town become
          unreliable. A weak shriner finds the hidden route, an adventurer clears the danger, and a
          guild worker rebuilds the object that lets the town remember how to travel again.
        </p>
        <p>
          This is the heart of the project: not chosen-one conquest, but the recovery of hidden
          infrastructure. The fantasy is survival, proof, repair, and collective memory.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="shell">
      <p class="eyebrow">Browse the cast</p>
      <h2>Representative characters and monster families</h2>
      <div class="card-grid">
        {homepageFeaturedCharacters.map((page) => <ShowcaseCard page={page} href={`characters/${page.slug}`} />)}
        {homepageFeaturedMonsters.map((page) => <ShowcaseCard page={page} href={`monsters/${page.slug}`} />)}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
